The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 Bengal slumped to a three-wicket defeat against Punjab in the CK Nayudu Trophy at the Jadavpur University, Salt Lake campus ground Thursday.       
	Resuming on an overnight score of 149/5, Bengal were dismissed for 278 on the fourth day. Apart from Writam Porel, who slammed 124, none of the Bengal batsmen could make any impact. Chasing 223, Punjab reached the target losing seven wickets to take home full points.      
	BRIEF SCORES      
	Bengal 251 amp; 286 (W. Porel 124; R. Singh 6/95). Punjab 315 amp; 226/7 (A. Singh 78; N. Das 3/25). Punjab won by 3 wkts.          
	 East Bengals new Ghanaian recruit Abel Hammond has triggered off a debate between coach Subhas Bhowmick and some other officials whether to register the player for the I-League.       
	While Bhowmick, one learns, is of the opinion that the player is yet to get into proper shape, some of the officials are insisting that the striker be signed.           
	 Chirag United suffered a setback Thursday as Australian recruit Keegan Nash has been ruled out for at least four months with an ankle injury that he picked up at practice. An MRI scan will be done Friday and a clearer picture will then be available.           
	CFL  BNR vs Kalighat Milan Sangha, Bagan from 2.30pm                                                                                                                                                                       
